description: A group of signs, symptoms, and clinicopathological characteristics that may or may not have a genetic basis and collectively define an abnormal condition.
label: syndromic disease

obo_definition_citation.definition: A group of signs, symptoms, and clinicopathological characteristics that may or may not have a genetic basis and collectively define an abnormal condition.

obo_synonym.name: syndrome associated with disease or disorder

synonyms: syndrome associated with disease or disorder

description: A disease that is caused by genetic modifications where those modifications are inherited from a parent's genome.

Usage note: this is intended only for diseases with an inherited genetic etiology. Somatic genetic mutations are excluded. Some ontologies use the term 'genetic disease' in the sense of inherited disorders only, we are here careful to distinguish.
label: hereditary disease

obo_definition_citation.definition: A disease that is caused by genetic modifications where those modifications are inherited from a parent's genome.

description: A disease involving the reproductive system.
label: reproductive system disorder

obo_definition_citation.definition: A disease involving the reproductive system.

synonyms: disease or disorder of reproductive system

description: 'psychiatric disorder' is not classified as a 'nervous system disorder' in Mondo (though it is often as such): the hallmarks of psychiatric disorders are based in behavior and emotional state, and the relation with nervous system malfunction or damage is not always clearly determined.
A non-neoplastic or neoplastic disorder that affects the brain, spinal cord, or peripheral nerves.
label: nervous system disorder

obo_definition_citation.definition: A non-neoplastic or neoplastic disorder that affects the brain, spinal cord, or peripheral nerves.

synonyms: disease or disorder of nervous system

description: Any condition related to a disturbance between proper intake and utilization of nourishment.
label: nutritional disorder

obo_definition_citation.definition: Any condition related to a disturbance between proper intake and utilization of nourishment.

description: A disease involving the endocrine system.
label: endocrine system disorder

obo_definition_citation.definition: A disease involving the endocrine system.

synonyms: disease or disorder of endocrine system

description: Clinical conditions caused by an abnormal chromosome constitution in which there is extra or missing chromosome material (either a whole chromosome or a chromosome segment). (from Thompson et al., Genetics in Medicine, 5th ed, p429)
label: chromosomal disorder

obo_definition_citation.definition: Clinical conditions caused by an abnormal chromosome constitution in which there is extra or missing chromosome material (either a whole chromosome or a chromosome segment). (from Thompson et al., Genetics in Medicine, 5th ed, p429)

description: Any disease or disorder that disrupts the process development of an anatomical structure. Can be due to genetic or environmental causes. Typically happens during embryogenesis, but also includes post-embryonic development.
label: disorder of development or morphogenesis
